Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora; orientation uncertain; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of undetermined curved and black motif with some added red, at left(?); at centre, possibly part of an animal's leg, to right; at right, undetermined black object and part of garment-like motif with red.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0062) (Phase 1)
